gov.cms.qrda.validator.model

Class ValidationSuite

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.cms.qrda.validator.model.ValidationSuite
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class ValidationSuite
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    The ValidationSuite class contains all of the information required to perform validation on a list of test files against a schematron. A ValidationSuite consists of the filename of a schematron, the schematron type (which also corresponds to names of subfolders in the QRDA file repository resident in the QRDA_HOME/qrda file space), and a list of TestCase objects. The ValidationService runs a validation test using an instance of ValidationSuite.
    Author:
    Dan Donahue
    See Also:
    ValidationService, Serialized Form

        Initializes the class instance. Create interim filenames for files that are generated during the validation process. Also creates the filename used for saving/serializing this instance to disc. The saved filename is of the form:

        name_timestamp.vs
